topic.title: Nokia BKP Interface

body.p: Refer to Table 1 for a list of device level pins that connect to the integrated IP blocks as per the pin name column. The device level pins map to pins of the integrated IP with the same name with the exceptions noted in Table 2.
For the AC timing characteristics of this interface, see Nokia BKP Interface.

entry.p: 125 µs framed Sync from CRU-A at 38.88 MHz.
Sampled on the rising edge of CK38A.
125 µs framed Sync from CRU-B at 38.88 MHz.
Sampled on the rising edge of CK38B.
Selected clock between CK38A and CK38B.
Selected sync between SYNCA and SYNCB.
Updated on the falling edge of CK38AB_SEL.
Active high output. When asserted, NO_CRU indicates that both CLK38_A and CLK38B are not present and that no reference clocks are recoverable.
Asynchronous active high input. When asserted, indicates that the distributed matrix channel is invalid.
When asserted high, OH_READY indicates to the device that the OH communications link is running without issue.
Port side OHI (input) data link at 1244.16 Mb/s.
System side OHI (output) data link at 1244.16 Mb/s.
General purpose inputs, used exclusively by Nokia IP.
General purpose outputs, used exclusively by Nokia IP.
